# Local context (example)

**Copy this file to `local-context.mdc`** (same folder). That path is in `.gitignore` so it never pushes.

Suggested sections (fill with your real details):

| Section | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **Persona** | Names, tone, how you like the assistant to address you |
| **Company & revenue** | What you build, metrics you’re OK keeping local |
| **Roadmap & ops** | GitOps repo names, cloud, priorities |
| **Security** | What “production” means for your stack |
| **Triggers** | Wake phrases + paths (e.g. resume repo, transcribe folder) |
| **Tooling** | Absolute paths only here, not in public rules |

The maintainer’s filled-in `local-context.mdc` is **not** in the repo—clone and create your own.
